abstract: The Israeli prime minister will face voters on March 2 as a defendant in a criminal case, but without weeks of potentially humiliating parliamentary discussion on the subject.
snippet: The Israeli prime minister will face voters on March 2 as a defendant in a criminal case, but without weeks of potentially humiliating parliamentary discussion on the subject.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has withdrawn his request for immunity from prosecution on corruption charges, he said Tuesday morning, complaining that he would not have gotten a fair shake from Parliament and had therefore “decided not to let the dirty game continue.”

abstract: Corrections that appeared in print on Tuesday, Jan. 28, 2020.
snippet: Corrections that appeared in print on Tuesday, Jan. 28, 2020.
lead_paragraph: An article on Monday about the purchase of newspapers by hedge funds misstated the name of the institution where Ann Marie Lipinski is the curator. It is the Nieman Foundation for Journalism at Harvard University, not the Nieman Center for Journalism.

abstract: John Bolton’s revelations, and the question of whether he would testify, loomed over the Senate trial.
snippet: John Bolton’s revelations, and the question of whether he would testify, loomed over the Senate trial.
lead_paragraph: Read our full story on the day, some key highlights and an analysis of the power Mr. Bolton’s book might have over the president.
headline_main: Impeachment Briefing: Day 2 of Trump’s Defense

abstract: The president’s picked-for-television defense team avoids a ratings “Death Valley,” then gets hit by a Bolton from the blue.
snippet: The president’s picked-for-television defense team avoids a ratings “Death Valley,” then gets hit by a Bolton from the blue.
lead_paragraph: President Trump, reportedly, wanted a telegenic team to make the case for him at his impeachment trial. But the biggest star in the Senate chamber on the first full day of his defense on Monday was The Man Who Wasn’t There.
